        "explanation": "The application.properties file at line 17 sets `management.endpoints.web.exposure.include=*`, which exposes ALL Spring Boot Actuator endpoints over HTTP to any actor without authentication or authorization controls. This includes sensitive endpoints such as `/actuator/env` (reveals environment variables and configuration properties including potential secrets), `/actuator/heapdump` (dumps the JVM heap), `/actuator/threaddump`, and `/actuator/beans`. Any unauthenticated user can access these critical management resources, allowing unintended actors to read potentially sensitive application configuration and runtime data."
